for free or reduced-price lunch, as determined pursuant to 42 U.S.C. §
1771; or
(B)
(i) Reside outside the geographic area served by the LEA;
(ii) Are children of a parent employed by the LEA; and
(iii) Are four (4) years of age on or before August 15.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-104, is amended by adding the
following as a new subsection:
(f) An LEA that authorizes a child to enroll in the LEA's voluntary pre-
kindergarten program pursuant to subdivision (c)(2)(B) may charge the child's parent
tuition and fees in an amount that is no more than the LEA's costs of the child enrolling
and attending the program.
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-107(d), is amended by adding ",
except as authorized pursuant to § 49-6-104(f)" after "§§ 49-6-103 — 49-6-110".
SECTION 4. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
